Landrover dealer sent quote:
Loud noise from the vehicle:

Tech Story: Performed road test, confirmed metallic crunching noise present at almost all times. Also noted difficulty moving forward after some time. Performed inspection of suspension and brakes, no abnormal wear or damage noted. Checked drivetrain operation on hoist, confirmed noise present from power transfer unit (PTU). Removed under shield and found that PTU has leaked heavily. Also noted that lower control module has melted from mounting points. Removed drain plug to PTU and found that there is no fluid remaining is unit, large metal flakes on magnetic plug. PTU has experienced internal failure, replacement is required. Vehicle is not able to drive.
            Parts: 6150.99 +tax 
            Labor: 6.00 hours- $1134.00


Also needs taillight and a timing cover plug.
I replied that the PTU is not covered due to lack of lubrication and the taillight and plug are simply not covered. A.H.
